9 great books by Raymond Chandler. Well, he has written only 8, but don't get scared; here are 3 in English, and 6 in my native language !  / It is BG /
===========
in English -  The Little Sister ; The Lady in the lake ; The High Window. 
A bunch of selected quotes as well.
==========
in BG - The lady in the lake ,Poodle Springs, The Long goodbay, Farewell my lovely, Playback, The big sleep  + a link to more e-books...
===========
Also u can find several small pictures of the covers.
Don't be surprised that the books are in .txt or .rtf or even .pdf format. That's what the free community uses -  WORDPAD / Notepad / free Office, no shitty software, thanks.
* * * * * * 
So, to sum up - Chandler, who died in 1959 &lt;a href=&quot; http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raymond_Chandler&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt; http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raymond_Chandler&lt;/a&gt; 
was a great story-teller, his masterpieces in detective genre are vivid, touching, fullsome, inspired, clever and really impressing even nowadays, and may be will stay wholesome and charming forever. As some famous detective said 'the methods are new, but the crimes and criminals are still the same'. Sadly true. Look around folks :(
Cheers anyway, seed and enjoy...
